The paper is about analyzing the program committee of a software engineering conference, which falls under the software engineering subfield of computer science. Therefore, cs.SE is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses diversity and turnover, which could be relevant to the cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI) subfields. The analysis of paper authorship and collaboration could be relevant to the programming languages and compilers (cs.CC) subfield. Finally, the discussion of the needs and challenges of the program committee participants could be relevant to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) subfield.
